{
  "title": "Critical flaw found in older Cisco Small Business Routers won't be fixed",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "b3b861a0094708b1",
      "text": "A critical vulnerability in Cisco Small Business Routers will not be patched by the networking equipment giant, since the devices reached end-of-life in 2019."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "0883c7283cf8a3ab",
      "text": "Tracked as CVE-2021-34730 (CVSS score: 9.8), the issue resides in the routers&apos; Universal Plug-and-Play (UPnP) service, enabling an unauthenticated, remote attacker to execute arbitrary code or cause an affected device to restart unexpectedly, resulting in a denial of service (DoS) condition."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "2421370f12325907",
      "text": "The vulnerability, which the company said is due to improper validation of incoming UPnP traffic, could be abused to send a specially-crafted UPnP request to an affected device, resulting in remote code execution as the root user on the underlying operating system."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "9d17af639c65f80b",
      "text": "&quot;Cisco has not released and will not release software updates to address the vulnerability,&quot; the company noted in an advisory published Wednesday. &quot;The Cisco Small Business RV110W, RV130, RV130W, and RV215W Routers have entered the end-of-life process.  Customers are encouraged to migrate to the Cisco Small Business RV132W, RV160, or RV160W Routers.&quot; [https://tools.cisco.com/security/center/content/CiscoSecurityAdvisory/cisco-sa-cisco-sb-rv-overflow-htpymMB5 https://tools.cisco.com/security/center/content/CiscoSecurityAdvisory/cisco-sa-cisco-sb-rv-overflow-htpymMB5] [https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/products/collateral/routers/small-business-rv-series-routers/eos-eol-notice-c51-742771.pdf https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/products/collateral/routers/small-business-rv-series-routers/eos-eol-notice-c51-742771.pdf]"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "41eb8b5085dd8b8c",
      "text": "The issue impacts the following products &#8221;    - RV110W Wireless-N VPN Firewalls    - RV130 VPN Routers    - RV130W Wireless-N Multifunction VPN Routers    - RV215W Wireless-N VPN Routers [...]"
